118
00:08:14,945 --> 00:08:19,750
Here's a table summarizing some important
properties of elementary particles.

119
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:23,940
In the upper half of the table you
find the constituents of matter.

120
00:08:23,940 --> 00:08:28,590
Leptons and quarks are of
spin one half as you can see.

121
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:33,100
In the lower half you find
particles that transmit forces.

122
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:34,774
These are bosons of integer spin.

123
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:40,556
The charges are indicated in units of
an elementary charge for each one of them,

124
00:08:40,556 --> 00:08:43,821
like the one of the electron in
the case of the electric charge.

125
00:08:43,821 --> 00:08:48,621
Here we say that its charge
is -1 which means that it is 

126
00:08:48,621 --> 00:08:51,260
-1 times the elementary charge, e.

127
00:08:53,530 --> 00:08:59,780
The weak charge is called weak isospin and
it has two components

128
00:08:59,780 --> 00:09:03,810
in contrast to the electromagnetic
charge which has only one component.

129
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:07,291
We denote them by T and T3,

130
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:12,740
the total length of the weak isospin and
its third component.

131
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:19,290
This charge depends on the orientation of
the spin of the particle with respect to

132
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:25,040
its direction of motion, which means
it depends on the helicity of the particle.

133
00:09:26,470 --> 00:09:28,880
The strong charge has three components.

134
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:35,050
It's called color, and we use the
abbreviation r for red, g for green, and

135
00:09:35,050 --> 00:09:37,280
b for blue to denote them.

136
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,780
Color is a property of quarks and

137
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:44,730
of gluons where the latter even carry
a color and an anti-color simultaneously.

138
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:50,650
For every particle, there's an
anti-particle which has the same mass but

139
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:53,839
all charges opposite,
as indicated in this red table.

140
00:09:57,650 --> 00:09:59,440
Charges are additive quantum numbers.

141
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,390
For a system of particles
the total charge is the sum

142
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:04,640
of the charges of its constituents.

143
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:07,600
But there are other quantum
numbers that are conserved.

144
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:12,900
The first one quoted here is
the total number of baryons,

145
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:17,120
i.e. the number of baryons minus
the number of anti baryons in a system.

146
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,190
This number is conserved,

147
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:25,340
this applies in particular to quarks
which have a baryon number of 1/3,

148
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:29,710
and anti-quarks which have
a baryon number of minus 1/3.

149
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:34,215
The total lepton number, the number
of leptons minus the number of

150
00:10:34,215 --> 00:10:38,490
antileptons is also constant
in a closed system.

151
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:42,200
To a certain extent this is even
true generation by generation but

152
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,830
the neutrinos which show up here,
nu_e, nu_mu and

153
00:10:44,830 --> 00:10:48,960
nu_tau are mixtures of the true particles,
nu_L, nu_M and nu_H.

154
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:55,980
So, there's some mixture between
generations in weak interactions.

155
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,685
But more important than that,

156
00:10:57,685 --> 00:11:02,170
the charges of all types are rigorously
conserved as far we know.

157
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:06,110
This evidently concerns the electric
charge Q that you are familiar with but

158
00:11:06,110 --> 00:11:09,390
also the weak isospin T and

159
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:13,740
T3, and the color charges R, G, and B.

160
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:19,770
The flavor which distinguishes
between generations is a special case.

161
00:11:19,770 --> 00:11:23,140
It is conserved by the strong and
electromagnetic interactions but

162
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:24,579
can be altered by the weak one.

